  ** Nonsensical headline... (Score:2)
     (by JoeDuncan ( 874519 ))

     
     It's like saying "gold is worth more than money!" - totally
     meaningless.
     One (gold, developers) is a commodity that IS exchanged, the
     other (money) is the medium OF exchange.
     Saying that "commodity X" is worth more than "exchange medium Y"
     makes no sense because a commodity CANNOT be worth "more" or
     "less" than the medium of exchange used - it can only ever be
     worth a specified amount of Y.

